author: Wires English | Indo-Asian News Service
title: Taylor Swift earns $1 million per day
text:
Taylor Swift earns $1 million per day By Indo-Asian News Service on October 19, 2015 at 2:13 PM Comments 
Los Angeles, Oct 19: Singer Taylor Swift reportedly earned $1 million per day so far in 2015. The “Bad Blood” hitmaker raked in $317.8 million since January thanks to her “1989” album and world tour and endorsement deals, according to the Sunday Express. And this made Swift highest-paid musician in the world after reportedly earning more than $1 million a day so far in 2015, reports dailymail.co.uk. (Read: Karan Johar proud of Alia Bhatt, Sidharth Malhotra and Varun Dhawan) 
LA-based media analyst Mike Raia said: “Right now, Taylor is untouchable. She is so far ahead of everyone else in the industry that she has become not only a powerhouse entertainer but also an important mover and shaker on the commercial side of the music business.” This comes after Swift and her boyfriend Calvin Harris were recently named the world’s highest-paid celebrity couple.
